    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://adamconkey.github.io/home/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Apr 2016 00:00:00 -0600</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://adamconkey.github.io/home/about/</guid>
      <description>Biography I am a PhD student in the School of Computing at the University of Utah in the robotics track of the Utah Robotics Center. I work in the Utah Learning Lab for Manipulation Autonomy (LL4MA) and am advised by Dr. Tucker Hermans. My research focuses on learning manipulation tasks from human demonstration with a targeted application to the problem of robust teleoperation over large latency.
I am looking for internship opportunities for Summer 2019 in robotics, machine learning, or software development.</description>
    </item>
    
